IMMEDIATE LEAD GENERATION (Start This Week)
High-Intent Lead Sources - Prioritized by Conversion Rate:

1. WhatsApp Business Groups (Hottest Leads - 30-40% Conversion)

Join 15-20 active car buying/selling groups in Kampala
Search: "Cars for Sale Uganda," "Car Import Uganda," "Dubai Cars Uganda"
Post daily: "Just landed: 2018 Toyota Harrier, 45K km, UGX 68M. Video available. DM for details"
Respond within 5 minutes - speed kills in these groups
Don't spam - provide value, answer questions, establish expertise
2. Facebook Marketplace & Groups (25-35% Conversion)

List every vehicle individually on Marketplace with detailed specs
Join groups: "Cars in Uganda," "Kampala Sell and Buy," "Uganda Auto Traders"
Post high-quality photos + "CALL NOW" with phone number
Run boosted posts (UGX 50K-100K/week) targeting Kampala, 25-50 years old, interested in cars
Use Facebook's "Send Message" button - conversations convert better than comments
3. Direct Outreach to Corporate Clients (40-60% Conversion)

Target companies needing fleet vehicles: NGOs, telecoms, banks, logistics companies
Cold call/email 10 companies per day offering fleet discounts
Pitch: "We import directly from Dubai, 15% cheaper than dealerships, full documentation support"
Offer to bring vehicles for test viewing at their offices
B2B deals are larger but slower - plant these seeds early
4. Referral Network (50-70% Conversion)

Partner with mechanics, insurance agents, SACCOS, car dealers selling NEW cars
Offer them 3-5% commission on successful sales
Mechanics know when clients need replacements
Insurance agents know accident victims needing new cars
New car dealers can refer budget-conscious clients to you
5. Physical Signage & Yard Presence (20-30% Conversion)

Large visible signage on main roads: "DUBAI CARS - DIRECT IMPORT - CALL [NUMBER]"
Park 2-3 cars strategically on busy roads with "FOR SALE" + phone number
Weekend open yard: Saturdays 9AM-6PM attract serious walk-ins
Simple banners: "2018-2022 Models | Toyota, Nissan, Honda | Fresh from Dubai"
YOUR DAILY SALES ROUTINE (Non-Negotiable)
Morning (8AM - 12PM): Prospecting Block

8:00-9:00: Check and respond to overnight inquiries (WhatsApp, Facebook, calls)
9:00-10:30: Make 20 outbound calls to yesterday's leads who didn't convert
10:30-12:00: Post fresh inventory on all platforms + engage in groups
Afternoon (12PM - 5PM): Customer Meetings & Follow-ups

12:00-2:00: Yard appointments (pre-scheduled test drives)
2:00-3:30: Follow up with warm leads (sent quotes but haven't decided)
3:30-5:00: Corporate visits or networking meetings
Evening (5PM - 8PM): Digital Engagement

5:00-6:30: Respond to new inquiries (peak browsing time)
6:30-7:30: Create content (car videos, customer testimonials)
7:30-8:00: Plan tomorrow's outreach list
Target: 30-50 new conversations daily = 5-10 hot leads = 1-2 sales weekly

THE SALES CONVERSATION FRAMEWORK
Phase 1: Qualify Fast (First 2 Minutes) Questions to ask immediately:

"What type of vehicle are you looking for?" (Make/model)
"What's your budget range?" (Eliminates tire-kickers)
"When are you planning to buy?" (This week/month/just browsing)
"Will you need financing or paying cash?" (Affects deal structure)
If they're qualified (budget + timeline + serious), move to Phase 2 immediately

Phase 2: Build Desire (Next 5-10 Minutes)

Send 3-5 photos/videos of exact vehicle they want
Share WhatsApp status: "Customer picking up their Harrier today" (social proof)
"We have 3 people interested in this one, but you reached out first"
Emphasize: Fresh import, low mileage, full service history, inspection report available
Compare your price to established dealers: "At Bond Motors this is UGX 85M, we're offering UGX 72M"
Phase 3: Handle Objections (Next 5 Minutes)

Common objections and responses:

"Your price is too high"

"Compared to where? Let me show you the cost breakdown..."
"What price works for your budget? Let's see what we can do"
Offer: "I can reduce by UGX 2M if you commit with 50% deposit today"
"I need to think about it"

"Absolutely! What specific concerns do you have that I can address?"
"This vehicle won't last - 2 other clients viewing tomorrow. Can I hold it for you with a refundable UGX 1M deposit?"
"I want to see more options first"

"Smart approach! What exactly are you comparing - price, model, or year?"
"I'll send you 3 alternatives in your budget right now. Which works best?"
"How do I know this car is good quality?"

"Great question! Here's the Dubai inspection report, here's the service history, and we offer 3-month warranty"
"You can bring your mechanic to inspect before final payment - we encourage it!"
Phase 4: Close (Next 2-5 Minutes)

Assumptive Close:

"Perfect! Let's get your details for the reservation. Full names as they appear on ID?"
"Should I register this under your personal name or company?"
Alternative Close:

"Would you prefer to pick it up this Friday or next Monday?"
"Are you paying full amount or would you like our 40% deposit plan?"
Urgency Close:

"I have another client coming at 3PM to view this same car. Can you commit now with UGX 5M deposit to secure it?"
"This model just arrived and we typically sell these within 3-4 days"
Trial Close:

"If I can get this down to UGX 70M, would you take it today?"
"What's the one thing stopping you from moving forward right now?"
CLOSING TECHNIQUES THAT WORK IN KAMPALA
The Deposit Strategy:

Make it easy to commit: "Just UGX 1-2M deposit holds it, refundable if inspection fails"
Accept Mobile Money on the spot: "Send to [number] now, I'll send receipt immediately"
Never let them leave without SOME commitment: "Can you at least put UGX 500K to show you're serious?"
The Comparison Close:

Show them printouts of same car at Bond Motors, SBT, Toyota Uganda (higher prices)
"You're saving UGX 10-15M buying from us - that's why we sell fast"
Create comparison table on your phone, show live
The Finance Partnership:

Pre-arrange with Centenary Bank, DFCU, or SACCOS
"I can connect you with our finance partner - approval in 48 hours"
"They need just 30% down, you can drive away this week"
The Trade-In Close:

"What are you driving now? We can take it as part payment"
Overvalue their trade-in slightly to make deal sweeter
"Your car is worth UGX 25M, so you'd only top up UGX 45M for this one"
LEAD TRACKING & FOLLOW-UP SYSTEM
Use Simple Google Sheet or Notion:

Columns:

Name | Phone | Vehicle Interest | Budget | Inquiry Date | Status | Next Action | Notes
Status Categories:

HOT (ready to buy within 7 days) - Follow up daily
WARM (interested, 2-4 weeks timeline) - Follow up every 3 days
COLD (just browsing, 1+ months) - Follow up weekly
DEAD (no budget/not serious) - Remove from active list
Follow-Up Sequence for Warm Leads:

Day 1: Initial conversation + send vehicle details
Day 2: "Hi [Name], did you get a chance to review the Harrier details I sent?"
Day 4: Send new arrival: "Just got this 2019 model you might prefer..."
Day 7: Call: "Any questions I can answer? Would you like to schedule viewing?"
Day 10: Price drop urgency: "Reducing this by UGX 2M this weekend only"
Day 14: Final attempt: "We have a buyer for this one. Still interested or should I let it go?"
The Fortune is in the Follow-Up:

80% of sales happen after the 5th contact
Most importers give up after 1-2 attempts
Your persistence = your competitive advantage
