MESSAGE 10: RISKS & HOW WE MITIGATE
REAL TALK - THE RISKS:

I'm not sugarcoating this. Here are the dangers:

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 1: Buying Damaged Cars in Dubai
Solution: ALWAYS use third-party inspection. Never skip. Budget UGX 200-300K per inspection.

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 2: Currency Fluctuation (USD/UGX)
Solution: Price in USD or update weekly. Hedge with forward contracts for bulk orders. Keep 6-month cash buffer.

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 3: Import Duty Increases
Solution: Stay connected with importers association. Diversify income streams. Don't over-leverage.

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 4: Customer Defaults (Don't Pay After Arrival)
Solution: 40-50% deposit BEFORE ordering. Clear contracts. Legal recourse.

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 5: Competition (Established Importers)
Solution: Superior service, transparency, online presence, partnerships. We're more agile.

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 6: Scam Suppliers in Dubai
Solution: Visit Dubai personally first. Vet suppliers thoroughly. Start small, build trust.

‚ö†Ô∏è RISK 7: Cash Flow Crunch
Solution: Never buy more inventory than we can afford to hold for 3 months. Working capital discipline.

INSURANCE WE NEED:
‚úÖ Marine cargo insurance (vehicles in transit)
‚úÖ Vehicle stock insurance (at our yard)
‚úÖ General business insurance
‚úÖ Public liability

BIGGEST RISK? Us not executing properly. 

The business model works - importers make millions. We just need to:
1. Work harder than competitors
2. Be more professional
3. Follow up relentlessly
4. Never compromise on quality
5. Build trust systematically

Thoughts on risk tolerance?
